-- ENRC Chairman Hires Adviser for Split Plan, Telegraph Says
-- B y   I s a a c   A r n s d o r f
-- 2012-08-12T06:42:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-12/enrc-chairman-hires-adviser-for-split-plan-telegraph-says.html
Eurasian Natural Resources Corp. (ENRC) ’s
chairman hired an adviser for a plan to split the mining
company, according to the Sunday Telegraph.  Mehmet Dalman recruited Amre Youness, who worked on the
company’s flotation and runs a holding company for the founders’
investments, the newspaper reported, without saying where it got
the information.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Isaac Arnsdorf in London at 
 iarnsdorf@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
